    "body": "There's one thing though... IIRC, parity had a consensus issue, related to the order in which they did certain things. A 'forbidden' op was invoked, but with too few stack items. Depending on whether they errored on 'shallow stack' or 'write protected', they reverted back to the wrong scope. \r\nI don't recall the exact details, but might be something we need to have in mind when doing this. \r\n\r\nAs for trace changing, I'm not sure that matters. The differential fuzzers don't care about the wording of the error messages. \r\n ",
