    "body": "> IIRC, parity had a consensus issue\r\n\r\nIt was this: https://github.com/openethereum/parity-ethereum/pull/6889/files \r\n\r\nSo if the balance was too low, the create/call simply failed. So remained in the same scope, but with a `0` on the stack. Whereas it _should_ have dropped back one level due to write-protection. If we just move the check slightly into the ops themselves, that should be fine, as long as we check write-protection before balance. \r\n",
